The Power Rangers travel to California in search of their new master and find him running a pizza parlor – so they join the staff to be trained.
As demons rumble from their graves beneath Mariner Bay, a government organization called Lightspeed recruits five civilians to defend the city.
Five teenagers, transformed by the mystical powers of the Quasar Sabers into the Galaxy Power Rangers, battle the evil Scorpius and Captain Mutiny.
When the wicked Undead Army is unleashed, sorceress Udonna empowers five teenagers – the Mystic Force Power Rangers – to save mankind.
When the elite warriors from the Wind Ninja Academy are captured by the evil Lothor, Shane, Tori and Waldo become Wind Power Rangers to fight back.
To keep powerful jewels from falling into the hands of two wicked brothers, five young Power Rangers set out on a dangerous global adventure.
The Power Rangers' new member, Dillon, isn't sure he wants to be on the team until he has a dream that sets the Rangers into action.
When the Troobian Empire attacks Earth, the B-Squad Power Rangers Space Patrol Delta morphs into action to squash the alien threat and save the world.
A new generation of Power Rangers must master the Symbols of Samurai Power, which give them control over the Earth's elements to battle dark forces.
Armed with a key that allows them to morph into any team of Legendary Rangers from the past, the Super Megaforce Rangers fight ruthless Prince Vekar.
The Samurai Power Rangers continue their battle against the evil Master Xandred, who has now joined forces with the malevolent Serrator.
The team launches a new campaign against evil in the year 3000, when the imprisoned criminal mastermind Ransik is freed by his daughter.
The Rangers use high-tech battle cars to take on Queen Divatox and her Divazords, who mount an attack on the Rangers' beloved Angel Grove.
Raised in the wilderness, young Cole Evans leads the Wild Force Power Rangers as they summon their animal powers to battle the evil Master Org.
This "Mighty Morphin Power Rangers" spinoff finds Tommy and the gang battling new enemies, using abilities acquired from the Zeo Crystal.
When Earth is threatened by a massive alien invasion, the planet's supernatural guardian calls upon five teenagers to form the ultimate defense team.
A prince and a commoner who are best friends keep having to thwart the plots of the prince's scheming, ambitious minister.

Titulo: Prohibition: A Film by Ken Burns and Lynn Novick
Enredo: Ken Burns's documentary traces the passage of the 18th Amendment, the social and legal effects of prohibiting alcohol, and the repeal of Prohibition.
A Spanish con man masquerades as a therapist and starts leading group sessions in Argentina for a crew of gullible misfits.
From teen lovers defying social and religious taboos to a student falling for her teacher, these stories explore joy and heartache in modern romance.
Javier is happily in love with Sofia, so when she breaks up their perfect life, he has to get her back – or maybe try finding a new perfect love.
Sparks begin to fly when a successful 33-year-old single woman and a 25-year-old romantic with few prospects navigate love and differences.
Eight women perform in front of celebrity judges and compete for the title of India’s top female stand-up comedian.
No "ism" is left unturned in this celebrity game show that battles stereotypes and sexism by pitting male and female comedians against each other.
A complex love triangle goes horribly wrong in this epic, multigenerational saga involving romance, revenge, mistaken identity and amnesia.
A prince's divine destiny to rule as a king is thwarted by his stepmother's scheme to put her own child on the throne in this legendary epic.
This sweeping historical drama charts the rise of a remarkable real-life figure, the first woman to ever rule the Delhi Sultanate.
Five friends from college chase their post-grad dreams of becoming a successful writer, film director, singer, rich wife and out-and-proud hair stylist.
Six students at an exclusive prep school, some on scholarship, discover that music can close the class divide.
Convicted of rape and murder at age 18, Daniel Holden spends nearly 20 years on death row until DNA evidence brings the verdict into question.
This parody of first-person shooter games, military life and science-fiction films centers on a civil war fought in the middle of a desolate canyon.
Award-winning filmmaker Reggie Yates travels around the world tackling big issues such as gun violence, racism, gay rights and addiction.
A pair of father and son private investigators tries to keep their combustible personal lives in check while tackling an intriguing array of cases.
After a mother and her daughter are gang-raped by seven men, the daughter suffers a mental breakdown, and the single mom sets out to get revenge.
Popular fairy tales take on a darkly comic edge in these short animated films based on a book by Roald Dahl and illustrator Quentin Blake.
This reality series follows the lives of a group of wealthy, successful Latina women in Los Angeles.
It's been six months since the last Jack the Ripper killing, and East London is hopeful that his reign of terror might have run its course.
Partners at an Indian matrimonial agency face endlessly challenging and often impossible demands as they help clients make the perfect match.
When a mysterious spaceship crashes in the Pacific, the people of Earth work to master the science of robotechnology and rebuild the giant fortress.
High school senior Belle pursues a shy junior boy. Dog-phobic Emma meets a handsome veterinary student. Baking blogger Mielle falls for her critic.
Dr. Hank Lawson unexpectedly gets a career upgrade as a freelance physician treating New York's aristocratic upper crust in their posh Hamptons homes.
Ruby, jealous of her wealthy best friend Maribel, cooks up a scheme to marry a millionaire. Hector, Maribel's boyfriend, is her target.
A nomadic swordsman arrives at a martial arts school in Meiji-era Japan, where he lands in the middle of a conflict involving the opium trade.
A four-part docu-series that's an exclusive, backstage pass to global comedy superstar Russell Peters' record-breaking "Notorious" world tour.
An arranged engagement between a village girl and her city cousin shows signs of true love, but an indiscretion decades ago could doom their romance.
Young musicians from 13 states in India demonstrate their cultural heritage by performing regional folk music using traditional instruments.
Pet rescue expert Rocky Kanaka and renovation specialist Rob North travel across North America, transforming animal shelters to help homeless pets.
A powerful team of Washington, D.C. lawyers makes scandals disappear while handling government crises and coping with problems of their own.
A married middle-aged woman is swept off her feet, both romantically and artistically, by a gifted young pianist.
Davina and Al try to revamp their lives as they struggle with the uncertainties of middle age in this darkly comic adaptation of the British hit.
After a Ukrainian high school teacher's tirade against government corruption goes viral on social media, he finds himself the country's new president.
This documentary series explores the explosive 2006 murder case of a 13-year-old Israeli girl and the subsequent conviction of a Ukrainian immigrant.
This miniseries recounts the early 19th-century conflict between the expanding British Empire in Africa and Shaka, the leader of the vast Zulu Nation.
In this updated take on Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's beloved mystery tales, the eccentric sleuth prowls the streets of modern London in search of clues.
Armed with a healthy sense of humor and the help of his teacher, friends and family, curious kid Sid tackles questions youngsters have about science.
Forced to become an apprentice cop, cocky playboy Igor finds he's got a knack for police work. But his job soon takes him down a dark personal path.
Inspired by a true story, this TV drama shadows a young Colombian woman who goes to shocking lengths to escape a life of poverty.
Born into a small town controlled by the mafia, an irate young woman seeks revenge on the forces that tore apart and wrongfully imprisoned her family.
Artists test their creativity and body painting skills as they face off in a series of elaborate challenges, vying for a grand prize of $100,000.
In each episode of this "Skin Wars" spinoff hosted by RuPaul, talented artists from various fields compete in body art for the first time.
Welcome to the irreverent world of Robert Hall – aka Slobby Robby – a pop culture junkie who buys and sells collectable goods from the '80s and '90s.
When freshman engineering student Kongpob stands up to older bully Arthit, their confrontation soon leads to a deep attraction between the two boys.
Spaceships Eagle, Robyn, Hawk and their pals at the Stardust Space Academy rocket through the galaxy, teaching kids about the wonders of science.
A Thracian man is condemned to a brutal death in the arena, only to outlast his executioners and be reborn as the enslaved gladiator Spartacus.
Curious pals Splash, Bubbles, Dunk and Ripple have fun exploring new places, making new friends and learning all about their amazing ocean home.
The passionate love between an alien boy and a human girl grows more and more dangerous as they face the wrath of their families and communities.
Ex-con Joris returns to his Swiss hometown, a community obsessed with American culture and ideals, to start over and save his family's gas station.
Six teenage groms come together one summer to share a dream: to work at the world-renowned Surfer's Paradise Resort on the legendary Sunset Island.
Woody sets out to become the Stone Age's best animal trainer with a little help from his faithful pet dinosaur, Moga.
In Canada, a colorful collection of treasure-seeking scavengers bid on the largely unknown contents of repossessed and abandoned storage units.
Join Strawberry Shortcake and her berry best friends in the whimsical land of Berry Bitty City, where they learn about teamwork and decision-making.
Born with supernatural strength, Bong-soon fights evil and procures justice while getting tangled in a love triangle with her CEO boss and cop crush.
From Spain's countryside to Scotland's stony terrain, this collection of uplifting documentaries explores the cultural roots of great strongman traditions.
In this 3D-animated spinoff from the Chhota Bheem series, valiant superhero Bheem goes beyond his village to fight the good fight across the universe.
A cheerful jet and his transforming pals strive to find peaceful solutions to their problems while delivering packages to children around the globe.
This series examines the aerodynamics of flight and the evolutionary processes that have enabled certain species to survive by taking to the skies.

Titulo: Surviving R. Kelly Part II: The Reckoning
Enredo: As more women come forward with harrowing accusations against R. Kelly, his criminal case gains momentum in this follow-up to the powerful docuseries.

Titulo: Swami Baba Ramdev: The Untold Story
Enredo: Born into poverty and denied an education, a village boy overcomes society’s obstacles to become India’s foremost spiritual guru, revered by millions.
Aliens fleeing their planet land on Earth, pose as teenagers and fight off mutant space monsters by joining forces to become a powerful giant robot.
After a personal tragedy upends his life, a highly skilled former Green Beret is drawn into a career as a secret government operative.
In 1976, naive Mary Ann Singleton moves to San Francisco and finds a new family in her bohemian landlady and the eclectic residents at 28 Barbary Lane.
We all want so much more than we have, but how far are we willing to go to get it?

Titulo: Th Eena Meena Deeka Chase Comedy Show
Enredo: A hungry fox and three resourceful, surprisingly formidable birds turn the animal kingdom on its head in this lively animated series.
From controversial cartoonist to powerful Mumbai politician, this biopic maps the meteoric rise of far-right Shiv Sena party founder, Bal Thackeray.
Feel groovy in 1970s suburbia, where a teen and his pals hang in the basement, listening to rock and indulging other hazy benefits of '70s culture.
Examine the triumphs, tragedies, cultural shifts and technological leaps that occurred during the millennium's first decade.
An insurance adjuster investigates cases of possible fraud while hiding a romance with a colleague, unaware that someone he trusts is toying with him.
Imagine your worst fears, then multiply them: Figaro is a boy with any number of phobias and a highly quirky and imaginative way of dealing with them.
Homespun humor and easygoing Sheriff Andy Taylor are at the center of this nostalgic look at Mayberry, a small town filled with lovable characters.
With their eyes on the grand prize, amateur designers push their creative limits in this reality competition show hosted by design icon Jamie Durie.
A single man searches for his soulmate through a series of dates with 25 contestants ready to romance him for a chance at love.
The artistic pursuits of two childhood friends, an aspiring singer and a talented dancer, lead them to four other 20-somethings in a drumming group.

Titulo: The Beginning of Life: The Series
Enredo: Using breakthroughs in technology and neuroscience, this series examines how environment affects infants – and how infants can affect our future.
Host Francesca Stavrakopoulou travels across the Middle East, offering extraordinary insights into the stories of the Old Testament.
In a global competition, eight fishing enthusiasts battle extreme conditions and dangerous waters to be crowned the ultimate angler.

Titulo: The Blue Planet: A Natural History of the Oceans
Enredo: David Attenborough narrates this definitive exploration of the marine world, from the familiar to the unknown, revealing the sea and its communities.
This documentary follows British bomb disposal teams in Afghanistan and the dangers they face in their methodical lives on the front lines of war.
Food-crazed travel junkies journey across India, completing bucket list challenges for a chance to win a once-in-a-lifetime scholarship.
Home cooks face off against trained chefs to see if passion can beat profession in the kitchen in this reality competition show.
In this three-part documentary series, host Marcus du Sautoy examines the mathematical code underlying all of life on Earth and the universe itself.
Thirtysomething career woman Jae-yeong attempts to juggle her job and personal relationships, all the while never failing to eat well.
On an ominous island off of Nova Scotia, two brothers chase historical theories on a quest for enigmatic treasure.

Titulo: The Day My Butt Went Psycho!
Enredo: A boy and his best friend – his newly detached butt – embark on wacky adventures in a world where humans and their butts live side by side.
Thwarted in their attempt to take over the world of Ente Isla, Satan and his general Alciel land in modern-day Tokyo, where they take on human form.

Titulo: The Drunk and on Drugs Happy Funtime Hour
Enredo: A variety-show production trips up big time when the cast members take their roles to new heights, and the line between fact and fiction blurs.
This nostalgic documentary series relives the 1980s from a variety of angles, exploring its impact on the politics, technology and culture of today.
Richie Beckett is an aging Brighton crime boss who's struggling with the onset of dementia, just as a rival gang is trying to take over his territory.
This offbeat drama charts the ups and downs of an interracial lesbian couple and their multiethnic brood of biological, adopted and foster children.
Elmo hops across the pond to help his extended monster family solve problems at their "almost" world-class establishment, the Furchester Hotel.
A look at the deeply intertwined history of humanity and fresh water reveals looming challenges that could upend power structures around the world.

Titulo: The Golden Years with Javed Akhtar
Enredo: Writer, poet and lyricist Javed Akhtar hosts this musical trip down memory lane, revealing untold stories behind India's best songs of 1950-75.

Titulo: The Great British Baking Show: Masterclass
Enredo: Hosts Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood leave the tent and go into the kitchen to put their professional spin on baking techniques used in the show.
This two-part tale delivers the true story of the Great Train Robbery of 1963, the biggest one in England's history.
Fantasy and reality collide when a surprisingly diverse group of online video-game addicts struggle to balance the game with personal relationships.
Panelists from the Korean show "Abnormal Summit" lead cast mates on tours of their home countries, including China, Nepal, Italy, Canada and France.
With host Vinay Pathak, Indian celebrities return to their childhood homes to reconnect with the past and share stories of their journey to success.
Witness some of the most riveting showdowns in the animal kingdom as cameras capture leopards, polar bears and other predators targeting their prey.
This rib-tickling series follows four English lads as they try – and fail spectacularly – to navigate the wretched no-man's land of adolescence.

Titulo: The Investigator: A British Crime Story
Enredo: After 40 years of inconclusive evidence, renowned criminologist Mark Williams-Thomas re-examines a string of mysterious murders.
This documentary crime series charts the rise of the Irish Mob in America, from urban immigrant poverty to political power and wealth.
Mexican journalist and UFO investigator Jaime Maussan travels the world collecting evidence and firsthand accounts of extraterrestrial phenomena.
Host Leon Logothetis travels the world with only a vintage motorbike and the kindness of strangers, which he pays back in unexpected, inspiring ways.
This trailblazing series follows the tangled lives and ever-changing relationships among a close-knit group of lesbians who call Los Angeles home.
The wife of a corporate heir finds her luxurious life overturned by a mysterious woman who joins the household as a caregiver for her father-in-law.
At the CARE detective agency, investigators see a lot of action but must always keep their cases secret, even when it affects their personal lives.
Exonerated in the murder of her father and stepmother, Lizzie Borden takes on crime lords, detectives and other foes as she savors her new infamy.
Documentary crew members brave Earth's most frigid regions to capture the majesty and mystery found in the chillier side of the animal kingdom.
A group of strangers who are killed by a mysterious object soon come back to life and learn they have been chosen to prevent the apocalypse.
Producer and narrator Anthony Bourdain explores the creative processes of international celebrity chefs to learn what fuels their culinary artistry.
Some have big feet or a sniffly nose, others are clumsy or too sweaty – but these kids soon discover their mini problems can become superpowers.
Three officers from different eras work for a secret agency guarding Spain's past from time-traveling intruders trying to manipulate history.
Brave people get onstage to read hilarious and humiliating tales of gawky teenage love, family dysfunction and other stories from their younger years.

Titulo: The Most Beautiful Hands of Delhi
Enredo: A stalled career, failed marriage and receding hairline drive a middle-aged Swedish man to try to revitalize his life by visiting India.
This series tracks the ups and downs of an 18-month investigation into the 2014 stabbing murder of teenager Nicholas Robinson in Bristol, England.
Hosts David Spade, Fortune Feimster and London Hughes welcome guests from the newest and biggest Netflix titles for fun conversations, skits and more.
This U.S.-focused series dives into the cultural and political changes that swept the last decade of the 20th century. Executive produced by Tom Hanks.
This hit comedy chronicles the foibles of disgruntled office workers – led by deluded boss Michael Scott – at the Dunder Mifflin paper company.
How was the scientific understanding of the ancients so advanced? A team of experts answers this and other questions in this fascinating series.
Examine the troubling history of football hooliganism and hear from real hooligans about their bitter rivalries and rowdiest brawls.
Swept up in political unrest during World War I, two sisters in St. Petersburg cope with turbulent romances as Russian history is made around them.
This series examines 1970s America, focusing on the major political and historical landmarks of the decade and the cultural response to those events.
An extraordinary sense of smell gives a crime investigator unique insight into solving mysteries, but his gift takes a toll on his personal life.

Titulo: The Story of God with Morgan Freeman
Enredo: Host Morgan Freeman explores religion's role in human history, how our beliefs connect us and possible answers to life's million-dollar questions.

Titulo: The Story of Us with Morgan Freeman
Enredo: Explore the forces of love, belief, power, war, peace, rebellion and freedom in this series about the ties that bind – and destroy – humanity.

Titulo: The Super Mario Bros. Super Show!
Enredo: Mixing live action and animation, this classic series brought the beloved Super Mario Bros. video game characters to television screens everywhere.
In this hard-hitting series, journalist Nelufar Hedayat travels the globe to expose an array of black markets, from guns and gold to human body parts.
All the splendor and scandal of England's 16th-century royal court comes to life in this series that follows notorious Tudor monarch Henry VIII.
Hosted by creator Rod Serling, this groundbreaking anthology series presents tales of the supernatural that are often tinged with social commentary.
Virtual and real worlds collide as a group of teenagers who are grappling with matters of the heart cross paths in a cafe and on an anonymous website.
Discover the secrets of the universe in this series that pairs animation with insights on distant planets, black holes and other celestial marvels.

Titulo: The Vietnam War: A Film by Ken Burns and Lynn Novick
Enredo: Ken Burns presents an epic 10-part, 18-hour chronicle of the Vietnam War, featuring the soldiers, protesters, politicians and families that lived it.

Titulo: The War: A Film by Ken Burns and Lynn Novick
Enredo: A seven-part series brings World War II to life through the harrowing personal accounts of soldiers and others from "typical" American towns.
This powerful political epic chronicles the triumphs and travails of White House senior staff under the administration of President Josiah Bartlet.
Libertine He-jie finds himself torn between the lovely Amanda and fiery Xiao-qian. But now he faces a new problem: arrogant rival suitor Cheng-en.
A group of teens searches for the dark truth behind their school's mysterious and brutal history.
A renowned actor who is still pining over the loss of his first real love writes an autobiography about his memories of her, hoping to reconnect.
In an otherworldly river town, a policeman follows the trail of a sinister force to save his community from deadly spells.
A decade after college, a wake reunites five female friends struggling with illness, infidelity, toxic in-laws, spousal abuse and other life issues.
Firsthand accounts, re-enactments and computer-generated graphics retell in detail Thailand's biggest news stories from the past.
In his tiny meadow village, curious little mouse Tip enjoys fun and adventure while learning about the world with his furry friends and family.
After a divorce and fatal career move, a classically trained British stage actor navigates single life with his odd roommate and takes on horrid jobs.
They’re robots that can transform into cars – and the Tobots are committed to fighting villains to protect the city and root out crime.
This series investigates mysteries that persistently elude scientific explanation, such as mythical creatures, UFOs, sacred sites and more.
Social media star Hayes Grier returns to North Carolina for a reality series packed with action sports, pranks and romantic escapades.
Australia's toughest tow truck operators work to keep Queensland's streets clear of overturned semis and other automotive disasters.
The complex historical figure of Leon Trotsky comes to life in this epic biography that depicts the tumultuous life of the Russian revolutionary.
The colorful and curious family of Twirlywoos bounces around their boat and visits new places, turning learning into adventures wherever they land.
Young women face up to their insecurities and circumstances, finding love and laughs along the way. Featuring a different storyline every season.
Three friends who study martial arts find themselves defending humanity from a criminal mastermind and his invading army from another dimension.
For these half-car, half-animal friends, each day in Zippy City is a chance to have fun, be creative and use teamwork to solve difficult problems.
After taking the blame for a patient death, an anesthesiologist battling psychiatric trauma fights to stay afloat in the corrupt hospital system.
Part live-action and part animation, this visually inventive series offers striking portrayals of some of the unsung heroes of World War II.
